This past weekend was a huge milestone for me as a portrait photographer. Being apart of such a beautiful night celebrating with so many talented photographers across the world. ( some as far as Australia ) I am so grateful for my business mentor because with out her I would not be where I am today. 
To my fellow photographers, especially those who may be struggling with operating your business, Im not writing this post to boast but rather to inspire you. 

I was once told that photographers don’t make a-lot of money especially being a woman in such a male dominate industry. I was also told that I would need to move my business to a more affluent area to charge luxury prices, as I’m not located in the most ideal area here in New Jersey.

I am here to say this is 100% NOT true. If you are passionate and believe in yourself and work hard, you will succeed. Also a big part of being successful is educating yourself on running a business. As artists it so easy to just focus on creating beautiful pictures. Unfortunately, beautiful pictures does not mean you will have a profitable running business. If you don’t know how to operate a profitable business, I STRONGLY suggest you educate yourself!
( Rise to the top, with Megan Depurio fb group is where you should start)

For those who have followed my journey these past several years, you know that I started my business taking photos on my phone for $25 . 7 long years later … here am standing amongst 200 successful entrepreneurs in photography industry.  We all start somewhere, it takes time to grow so be patient and persistent but most of all education is key! 

Last but not least my beautiful clients❤️

Thank you to all my clients throughout the years. Without you I would not be standing here today. You all inspire me be better photographer with each year that passes. Nothing gives me the greatest joy when my clients see their artwork from me printed for the fist time. There is something so impactful seeing you and loved ones printed to hold in your hands or displayed on your walls. So thank you so much for choosing me to capture your precious memories. 
I feel incredibly honored and blessed. Thank you 🙏 🖤
